    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener><dateline><placeName ref="pl0001">Downing</placeName> March 29<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1778</dateline></opener>
                <p>I thank you for y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> favor &amp; am sorry to say my
                    interest is too small to assist anybody. &amp; lament my incapacity to serve
                        <persName ref="pe0246">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Pope</persName>. As I
                    hate to refuse so I trust no one will give me an opportunity again. I may ask a
                    subscription to an ingenious manâ€™s works; but not a place.<note type="editorial">In his letter of March 14 1778, Paton had requested Pennant's assistance on
                        behalf of the Reverend Alexander Pope in securing his son's appointment as
                        succesor to the ministry of his parish in Reay.</note> Be so good as to read
                    &amp; forward the inclosed. I shall deliver likewise to <persName ref="pe0104">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Gough</persName>, <persName ref="pe0156">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Lows</persName>
                    <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0422">Fauna</title></bibl> &amp; <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0423">Flora</title></bibl>; so clame them
                    from him. I set out too morrow</p>
                <closer>&amp; am <lb/>D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Sir <lb/>truely yrs
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">T. Pennant</persName>.</signed></closer>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p><address>
                        <addrLine>To</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Paton</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>at the Custom house.</addrLine>
                    </address></p>
                <p>3/</p>
            </div>
        </body>
